<br>
Losing countless hours of gameplay to misjudgement, an accident, a glitch, or perhaps even some PKer with nothing better to do is unimaginable, I know -- but it might encourage you to think more carefully before doing something you wouldn't if you couldn't just hop right back into the game (although C.R.s help do this).<br>
<br>
I'm not saying I wish this was part of the ruleset, but have you guys ever thought of how your style of play would change if there were no second chances (well, maybe limited ressurections, and / or penalities for the formerly dead if they were ressurected)? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 483<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/21/02 11:58:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2179.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What if</span><hr size=1> Nobody would get very far. If a game has permanent death, it really has to be designed around it. If EQ death was just made permanent, people would just plain not reach higher levels, death is too common and easy to achieve in this game. <br>
<br>
However, purely hypothetically assuming that there was permanent death, and for some reason, people did make it above level 10, I think people would be extremely paranoid and would be highly reluctent to do anything even remotely dangerous. My guess anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 623<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/22/02 12:37:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2179.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What if</span><hr size=1> Yep... Zildrax hit it on the head.<br>
<br>
Perma-death is one of the most basic issues that determines game design from the ground up. You have to build around it - it would require a completely new game to incorporate that into Norrath. You couldn't just add it in now without destroying any semblance of game balance. It's not an alternate rules issue, it is one of the fundamental assumptions that all the code was designed around.<br>
<br>
Like perma-death possible games? Low-magic D&amp;D campaigns and Dragonstorm are two I know of offhand. If NWN actually incorporates 3rd Edition rules from the open-source d20 guidelines, perma-death is a distinct possiblity.<br>
<br>
